programme.desc: In this episode, Dr. Marty Jopson risks life and limb urinating on an electric fence. To top it off, our Go Large duo supersize a yo-yo and sees if it would go back up once it reaches the bottom.

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E10

programme.desc: An adventure spanning billions of years into the evolution of life and consciousness. A visit to a 100,000-year-old laboratory. We reveal the extraordinary challenges these animals must overcome, and how our changing world is making survival even tougher than before. From epic battles between wolves and bison, to nail biting showdowns between cheetahs and Thompson gazelle fauns, this is an epic tale of life and death in the planet's most dramatic wildernesses.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E8
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz are off to Derbyshire to rescue a 48 year old Italian supercar: a 1971 Lamborghini Espada. This remarkable car belongs to lifelong petrol head Ged who bought the car in 1977 for #4000 however when it eventually broke down Ged's aim of one day restoring it to its former glory ground to a halt when serious health issues got in the way. Will the boys from Car SOS be able to make Ged's dream come true?

programme.title: Egypt With The World's Greatest Explorer E3
programme.desc: After weeks of adventure Ran and Joe have finally reached the end of their journey, to the south is the border with Sudan. In this episode, Joe skirts the crocodile infested waters of Lake Nasser and tries his hand at sailing a traditional Egyptian Felucca. Finally, Ran and Joe say goodbye to this incredible country and its lifeblood, the River Nile, just as Ran did half a century before.

programme.title: Explorer S3E11
programme.desc: Phil Keoghan journeys to Spain to immerse himself in the world of the 'castellers,' who build human towers. Sal Masakela explores the risks of the cash only marijuana business. Mariana van Zeller investigates growing tension between grizzlies and humans. We examine why the color blue is rare in animals.

programme.title: Ultimate Survival WWII E4
programme.desc: Hazen Audel retraces the epic journey of an escaped POW, who evaded capture on the Nazi occupied island of Crete for more than a year during WWII.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E5
programme.desc: In 2011, almost a decade since the release of its last flagship model, the Murcielago, Lamborghini launched its latest creation – the Aventador. Megafactories visits its factory in northern Italy, to follow the story of its creation from conception to launch and to witness an incredible production process.

programme.title: Mega Food E6
programme.desc: With 1,200 people, culinary operations are the biggest department in the SeaWorld Orlando theme park complex. Supplying 13 restaurants, over 50 carts and kiosks and special event dining, it's a 24-hour operation that runs 365 days of the year. And just one of these venues serves over 1,000 people an hour. Enter the SeaWorld kitchens and experience a different side of Orlando's favorite theme park.

programme.title: Explorer S3E12
programme.desc: Phil Keoghan journeys to Zambia to help tag lions. Francesca Fiorentini investigates the cause of a rash of earthquakes in Oklahoma. Cara Santa Maria explores if we are breeding dogs to death. Ryan Duffy joins Cory Booker as he uncovers environmental racism. Jago Cooper reveals risks to the global chocolate supply and solutions underway to save it.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E2
programme.desc: An examination of the techniques and tactics Saddam Hussein used to rise from a low level enforcer to become the supreme leader of Iraq. Through his brutal use of violence, intimidation and torture Saddam Hussein managed to rule the nation for nearly a quarter of a century until he was finally deposed by US forces during the Invasion of Iraq in 2003. Few dictators loom so large in recent history.

programme.title: Mega Air E6
programme.desc: Before lights out to start the Formula 1 season in Australia, Mega Air gets rare access behind the scenes at F1 team Haas as they rush to pack tonnes of cars and gear for air freighting. We roar back into Formula 1's past as former world champion Kimi Raikkonen's car flies to the Middle East and life-saving, temperature-controlled pharmaceuticals are given an almighty battering by the elements on a 6000 mile to Singapore.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E1
programme.desc: National Geographic digital nomad Andrew Evans gets under the skin of Eastern Turkey, travelling from the ruined city of Ani to the stone circles of Gobekli Tepe, considered the world's oldest temple. Travelling the same roads that oriental spice and silk traders used for thousands of years he discovers how the many civilisations that passed through the region have left their mark on the food, culture and architecture of modern Turkey.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E3
programme.desc: Step inside the most frigid habitat known to Earth - the poles. Here, the planet's ultimate survivalists include whale-hunting polar bears, leopard-seal dodging penguins and a pack of Arctic wolves that bring down a pair of musk oxen. Polar species have evolved bodies and behaviours that help them combat the intense hostility of their habitats. But now, their world is changing so fast - literally breaking apart under their feet - and their resilience will be tested beyond the extreme.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E1
programme.desc: Can a single meal brighten a child's future? Can a school lunch bridge the gap in education? Let's go back to school with the Akshaya Patra Foundation and learn how the world's largest school lunch program is cooking up millions of meals and offering India's children a hopeful tomorrow, one plate at a time.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E8
programme.desc: The rule-breaking and revolutionary Nissan GT-R competes with the big boys from the supercar world using a combination of cutting-edge aerodynamics, hi-tech engineering and a handcrafted V6 engine. It's one of the most affordable supercars on the road – mass produced on a production line in Nissan's Tochigi mega factory.

programme.title: Mega Air E7
programme.desc: Mega Air follows the challenging journey of a 55-million-dollar batch of cancer pharmaceuticals, from Northern Ireland to Heathrow, for a flight to the US. An East Midlands Airport wildlife officer gets into a flap trying to scare birds from his runway. Two gigantic stone crushing machines, destined for an African mine, threaten to crush the monster Antonov 124 air freighter. We travel with a pushback driver at one of America's busiest cargo airports.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E2
programme.desc: To uncover Turkey's hidden gems, Digital Nomad and travel enthusiast Andrew Evans heads to Western Anatolia and the Aegean Region. Following the same ancient trade routes trodden by oriental trade and spice merchants thousands of years ago, he finds a treasure trove of ancient wonders. From mysterious mountain top statues to some of the most pristine Roman remains in the world, Andrew uncovers the secrets of ancient Turkey.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E3
programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Italian dictator Benito Mussolini to rise to power and turn Italy into the first fascist state. A master of propaganda, he dubbed himself 'Il Duce' (the leader) and delivered bombastic speeches in which he idealized a fascist culture and promised to return Italy to the grandeur of Ancient Rome. Instead he created a one-party dictatorship and kept his grip on power for two long decades.

programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Italian dictator Benito Mussolini to rise to power and turn Italy into the first fascist state. A master of propaganda, he dubbed himself 'Il Duce' (the leader) and delivered bombastic speeches in which he idealized a fascist culture and promised to return Italy to the grandeur of Ancient Rome. Instead he created a one-party dictatorship and kept his grip on power for two long decades.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E8
programme.desc: The rule-breaking and revolutionary Nissan GT-R competes with the big boys from the supercar world using a combination of cutting-edge aerodynamics, hi-tech engineering and a handcrafted V6 engine. It's one of the most affordable supercars on the road – mass produced on a production line in Nissan's Tochigi mega factory.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E1
programme.desc: Can a single meal brighten a child's future? Can a school lunch bridge the gap in education? Let's go back to school with the Akshaya Patra Foundation and learn how the world's largest school lunch program is cooking up millions of meals and offering India's children a hopeful tomorrow, one plate at a time.

programme.title: Mega Air E7
programme.desc: Mega Air follows the challenging journey of a 55-million-dollar batch of cancer pharmaceuticals, from Northern Ireland to Heathrow, for a flight to the US. An East Midlands Airport wildlife officer gets into a flap trying to scare birds from his runway. Two gigantic stone crushing machines, destined for an African mine, threaten to crush the monster Antonov 124 air freighter. We travel with a pushback driver at one of America's busiest cargo airports.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E2
programme.desc: To uncover Turkey's hidden gems, Digital Nomad and travel enthusiast Andrew Evans heads to Western Anatolia and the Aegean Region. Following the same ancient trade routes trodden by oriental trade and spice merchants thousands of years ago, he finds a treasure trove of ancient wonders. From mysterious mountain top statues to some of the most pristine Roman remains in the world, Andrew uncovers the secrets of ancient Turkey.

programme.title: 1989: The Year That Made Us E5
programme.desc: We didn't know it then, but in 1989, the digital age had begun. It was the year the first modern GPS satellites roamed above the earth, but most of us were looking down at another tech wonder that year: the Gameboy. The popular device paved the way for today's mobile lifestyle. Another little invention called the world wide web debuted in 1989 too. Filmmaker Kevin Smith and a host of tech insiders take you on a journey through space and time.

programme.title: 1989: The Year That Made Us E1
programme.desc: The War on Terror began in 2001, but the cause of this 17-year conflict can be traced back to 1989. In this episode of National Geographic's insightful 6-part series, former Secretary of State James Baker and retired General David Petraeus shed new light on the early birth of Islamic extremism in Afghanistan, and examine America's complex, on-going battle against this ever-changing ideological enemy that knows no borders.

programme.title: Ultimate Survival WWII E5
programme.desc: Survival expert Hazen Audel retraces the incredible survival journey of 4 American airmen, left stranded in Australia's remote Gulf Country after an ill-fated bombing mission during World War II. Hazen follows their desperate passage through one of the most isolated places on earth, as they navigated a brutal environment of deadly snakes, man eating crocs and searing heat, in a heroic attempt to get back to base.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures S1E6
programme.desc: In the last desperate days of the Third Reich, the city of Berlin was turned into a citadel to protect Hitler. A 30ft (10 meters) underground fortress surrounded by 13ft (4 meters) thick concrete walls, it's safe from any attack the Allies can throw at him from the air.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E6
programme.desc: This is the final cruise for Captain Russo and he must have the Costa Serena in perfect running order before the handover to a new captain. There is also a new itinerary and a week of intensive safety tests keeping the crew busy before he disembarks. With a new route comes a change in the entertainment schedule as well. Preparations are in full swing for the final voyage of the season.

programme.title: Nazi World War Weird E1
programme.desc: Robert Joe & Dr. Sam Willis are on a mission to uncover the secrets behind Heinrich Himmler's Wewelsburg Castle in Germany. The mystery shrouding the castle has given birth to bizarre pop culture fantasies. As RJ and Sam fill in the blanks of this mystery they visit other sites that Himmler was linked to in an attempt to reveal the depths of Himmler's mind.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E8
programme.desc: Canadian 21-year-old Christina Jocko is addicted to spending money, partying and taking drugs. But when she discovers opiates her life spirals into addiction. Out of work, out of money and out of luck - an offer of an easy $10,000 for running cocaine from Panama looks like a way out. But little does she realise the tempting adventure will cost her five years of her life.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E5
programme.desc: Meet China's most affectionate and vocal monkeys in the remote, seasonal forests of Central China. These mountain forests and all who live here, experience unpredictable and harsh weather in a land that can be covered in snow for 4 months of the year. Follow the journey of a baby Golden snub-nosed monkey during the first year of her life as she learns all about her forest home and battles the elements to survive.

programme.title: Tut's Treasures: The Last Pharaoh
programme.desc: The discovery of Tutankhamun's tomb in 1922 made headlines across the world sparking a global frenzy for Ancient Egypt. Crammed inside were over priceless artifacts of every type - from gold slippers to finely tooled daggers, the remains of chariots and the boy king's show-stopping solid gold death mask. But of all the 5,398 treasures from the tomb of Tutankhamun it's the ones that paint a picture of Tutankhamun's family that are the most unsettling. Particularly intriguing are two tiny mummified babies found in the tomb. Now being re-examined in the labs of the Grand Egyptian Museum, they give a chilling insight into the bizarre practices that kept the Pharaoh's dynasty in power and ultimately lead to its downfall. DNA analysis reveals the tiny fetuses are Tutankhamun's still born children - the offspring of an incestuous relationship between Tutankhamun and his sister. Similarly DNA evidence suggests Tutankhamun was also the result of incest whilst artifacts, hidden for yea.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E4
programme.desc: The planet's hottest habitats - our deserts - are getting even hotter, drier and bigger, yet a host of remarkable animals still survive in the harshest conditions, including cunning hyenas, pint-sized meerkats and sand-dwelling spiders. Follow their lives through a single day in the desert to appreciate how they deal with the sun's formidable power as it grows stronger with every passing minute.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E1
programme.desc: Gok travels around Barcelona and seeks Western Mediterranean cuisine in this episode. He attempts to make Barcelona sausages with the help of a professional artisan sausage maker. Also, Gok looks for the renowned Chinese restaurant in the territory where peking duck and dim sum are served distinctively in Spanish-style with its original appearance.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E1
programme.desc: June 1944. The Japanese are in retreat across the Pacific. Now, at the island of Saipan, they face a pivotal battle. If they lose, a deadly new American weapon - the B-29 long-range bomber - will be within range of Japan for the first time. But the Empire believes a mighty weapon of its own will win the battle - a deep-rooted tradition of aggression and sacrifice in battle. Can the Japanese warrior mindset prevail?

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E9
programme.desc: An expedition searches for the iconic wrecks of the Battle of the Pacific, including the ship that delivered the Hiroshima bomb, USS Indianapolis.

programme.title: Nasca Lines: Unlocking The Secrets
programme.desc: As Peruvian archeologists along the site of the famed Nasca Lines employed hi-tech drones to look for signs of looting and encroachment, they were surprised to discover new designs made by an older Paracas culture - originating before the time of Christ. New footage expands on these Paracas geoglyph discoveries even further, diving deeper to explore the theory of whether these glyphs were meant to glow under the light of a full moon.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E9
programme.desc: Australian hippy, Mark O'Brien is dissatisfied with life. He joins an ashram in India, lead by the infamous guru Osho, looking for enlightenment. But when a fellow disciple encourages Mark to join her in a plan to smuggle an exotic form of hash to Amsterdam, it sets of a chain of events that leads him to a very different commune; the notorious Yawanda Central Prison.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E12
programme.desc: In Naples, soccer isn't just a sport, it's a religion, and their fans are world renowned for their dedication, enthusiasm and creativity. David spends a Sunday with S.S.C. Napoli supporters, taking in the sights, sounds and foods (of course!) at Stadio San Paolo.

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E3
programme.desc: It's the culinary Thrilla in Manila as the celebrity chefs head to the Philippines.

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E4
programme.sub-title: If You Can't Stand The Heat, Get Out Of The Kitche
programme.desc: The temperature rises as the battle continues in sunny Ipoh, Malaysia.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E33
programme.desc: Ben creates a fiery Armaticianna Pizza at Fairholme on the OzPig, Dr Andrew Stevenson helps us to understand the different methods of energy transfer. He then meets Joel at the University of Queensland. Here they demonstrate how to make a quick, versatile, simple salad that takes Ben on a trip down memory lane to Spain.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E34
programme.desc: At Fairholme, Ben takes us back to the memory of being eight years old smelling pork belly cooking over charcoal, a family tradition over New Year. He shows us how to create a super simple dry rub for pork belly. We then switch over to friend and butcher Scotty who teaches us how to wrap the pork tightly to allow for shrinkage while cooking!

programme.title: Heathrow S4E1
programme.desc: King of the Passenger Experience Manager, Demi, dealing with some disgruntled Passengers, Check in Girls Carrie- Anne and Selina juggling love lives and broken baggage belts, and discover if Border Force Bob will let a young Brazilian student into the UK to visit his brother?

programme.title: Heathrow S4E2
programme.desc: At Heathrow a plane takes off or lands every 45 seconds and in this episode we learn the secrets of parking planes with a rookie and his ping pong bats. The King and Queen of Terminal 2, Demi and Sue, wrestle with a bare chested drunk and back at immigration Kat and Bob come across a visitor whose reason for entering the UK just doesn't add up.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E2
programme.desc: The ship faces a tough week with worsening weather, a safety inspection putting jobs on the line, unusual guests and many unexpected challenges. Hotel Director Attilio Sissa is on board to ensure food and beverage safety of the ship's bars and restaurants. Later in the grand bar some gentlemen undergo extreme makeover for a talent contest while the entertainers are preparing for a big show.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E7
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef ventures into the isolated Amazonian jungle of Peru with the Huachipaeri and Matsiguenka tribes, where he samples termites, worms and a host of medicinal plants.

programme.desc: Oaxaca is the undisputed culinary capital of Mexico, and Peter Kuruvita spends a week here sampling all this city has to offer, from cheese to tamales and even a serving of grasshoppers.

programme.title: Exploring Malaysia S2E1
programme.desc: In this episode, world-record-breaking sailor Jesse Martin embarks on an inspirational nautical adventure along Malaysia Borneo's north-eastern coast. Exploring a region rich in seafaring cultures, he immerses himself in the lives of the sailors, sea gypsies, fishermen and marine conservationists who share his passion for life on the open sea.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E11
programme.desc: The Palio del Casale, or Donkey Race, brings thousands of spectators and partiers to the town of Camposano. It's a weekend-long party based around old Italian tradition and light competition between neighboring towns, regions, and even countries. Amidst the music, great food and drink, David learns what it's really like to be a donkey jockey, and represents Canada in the race - with exciting results.

programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in the Mayan stronghold of the Yucatan Peninsula, major producer of one of the hottest chillies on earth - the Habanero, before heading to the state of Tabasco where chocolate has been consumed for thousands of years.

programme.desc: Hidden beneath the surface of a remote corner of Malaysia Borneo lies a parallel universe of such elemental beauty, mystery and strangeness that it feels like it belongs on another planet. Naturalist Nick Baker embarks on a subterranean adventure into the magnificent cave systems of Sarawak to discover how the local people and wildlife have adapted to a landscape that is riddled with holes.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E13
programme.desc: David meets his buddy Gianluca, who invites him to his families hometown of San Gregorio Armeno, a small town 90 minutes outside Naples. For five days straight, David, Gianluca and his family eat drink and celebrate family tradition, making tomato sauce, and hunting for truffles.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E1
programme.desc: California has one of the largest populations of Japanese people in America. Their life here and their transition into American culture hasn't been a smooth one. In this episode we uncover their trials, resilience and delicious healthy food.

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E5
programme.desc: The neck and neck competition reaches its climax as the chefs arrive in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia for the Grand Finale.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E43
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys finish their food crawl at Maq01, the newest luxury hotel in Hobart with 114 rooms, each room reflects a certain Tasmanian character trait, colourful and quirky, hearty and resilient, curious and creative, grounded yet exceptional and fighting believer. Each room tells the story of a Tasmanian character who exemplifies one of these traits. They sit down to try some dishes in the Old Wharf Restaurant on the ground floor with the head chef, Simon Pockran.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E44
programme.desc: Ben and the crew head west to the Tarkine Rainforest where they take part in the Bonorong Tarkine Trail. Here they have a chat with Trevor, expert Tarkine guide on the way up to camp, and Ben cooks up a Pipppie Curry also known as a clam curry.

programme.title: Heathrow S4E3
programme.desc: Heathrow is currently the busiest airport in Europe so medical emergencies and busy check-ins are the norm. Add in half term with rich Russian kids returning home from British boarding schools, and the biggest mobile crane stopping in the middle of a live airfield, and tonight's episode of Heathrow's Britain's Busiest Airport won't disappoint.

programme.desc: All things Eastern feature in this week's episode of Heathrow: Britain's Busiest Airport. Be it the arrival of some special cargo, a potential people trafficker flagged to Border Force, or the polar vortex that battered Britain in March affectionately called the beast from the east. Rookie Ian is also back – this time wielding a gun.

programme.desc: It is a busy week for Costa Serena because there is the lavish gala evening plan with a magic show. programme.desc: The Dive Detectives brave pirate and shark infested waters to try and locate the missing subs of WWII and find out why they sunk.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E5
programme.desc: Sara drives a jeep through the flooding Pentecost River to East Kimberley, soaking in unforgettable scenery of the Cockburn Range Mountain. She arrives at Home Valley, a sustainable and tourist destination to meet aboriginals. Whilst enjoying the outback lifestyle at Home Valley with bushwalks and fishing, Sara is inspired by the communal spirit to prepare a wooden-fire oven crocodile pizza.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E6
programme.desc: Sara meets up with a local blogger Kartika to kick off her Broome tour. After learning the multicultural history of Broome, Sara is excited to know more and invites Neville, one of the last remaining pearl divers, to cook a 'luggers' lunch together on the pearl diving boats. After a successful hunt in the knee-deep muddy waters, Sara cooks the crab on the famous cable beach.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E8
programme.desc: Guide Basira Yuseff introduces John to the wide array of traditional delicacies available at a popular street food market in Kuala Lumpur including a snack with his name on it, Roti John! He then visits a local chef who has shaken up the dining scene with his innovative takes on classic Malaysian dishes before going back to the UK to prepare a chicken curry dish with TV chef Carolina.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E14
programme.desc: Pablo explores more about Tiwas of Tharakunchi after learning that they are divided into two: The Tiwas of the Hills and Tiwas of the Plains. While he gets a chance to be among the Tiwas during the festivities Pablo is just blown away as he gets to know more about their food, cooking techniques, and their societal views.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E8
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef braves the frozen bleak wilderness of Western Mongolia where he joins the Kazakh eagle hunters on a quest for wild rabbit on horseback.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E35
programme.desc: Staying in a beautiful accommodation by the sea, Ben makes his easy, no mess Fajita Baked Salmon. Joel meets Ben by discussing a fun fact about physics and spatulas, giving a trick to try at home. Their location is the Union College where they put their ‘zucchini spiralizer' to the test for a yummy, simple dish.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E36
programme.desc: Ben shows us a super simple, cheap and easy dip that is a sure winner at any dinner party. Ben and Joel discuss the differences between raw garlic and cooked garlic and how to decide between which to cook with.

programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchens revisit the cold city of their youth, Harbin. The brothers swim in icy waters, make an ice sculpture, race down an ice slide, and drink in a bar made of ice, then visit the world famous Harbin Ice Festival.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E3
programme.desc: High protein, omega-rich seafood saved our species from its first threat of extinction, funded the American Revolution, and increasingly fuels our brains and muscle today. Market fish like cod and tuna defined entire eras of history but unsustainable practices are forcing us to redefine our commercial goals in the ocean. Current demand necessitates a change in our attitudes toward seafood.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E5
programme.desc: The journey continues along the course of the Yellow River. Harry is now with Camel nomads in the Alxa League, Inner Mongolia where he aims for the million dollar shot with camels against sunset. He also learns that it does rain in the desert and that crops do grow. Plus, he finds out more about Suo Suo and Congrong, the cash crop that would replace the traditional herding ways of desert nomads.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E8
programme.desc: Oaxaca is the undisputed culinary capital of Mexico, and Peter Kuruvita spends a week here sampling all this city has to offer, from cheese to tamales and even a serving of grasshoppers.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E37
programme.desc: Ben discusses the benefits to cooking with ethical free range chicken, and then teaches us how to break down a whole bird in a way that limits wastage. Ben then meets friend and scientist Joel and talk through a quick and easy pickling recipe to avoid wasted fresh vegetables at home.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E38
programme.desc: Ben and the crew head down to the beautiful East Coast of Tasmania, where he attempts to cook the 'perfect steak'. He leaves the steak on a bed of salt for two hours before cooking and explains it results in increased flavour, and a nice crust on top.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E3
programme.desc: Wuzhong, home to the largest Muslim community on the silk road, and of course China's best place to enjoy Chinese halal food. Jamie will learn an unusual breakfast recipe that's certainly not for the faint-hearted and face his hardest noodle challenge yet. He also will uncover the secrets to the healthy yellow riverbank lifestyle that's helped shape the rich culinary history here an also got the younger generation rethinking their diets.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E4
programme.desc: Next stop, Dunhuang, the last city that trade merchants would pass through on the ancient silk road before braving the desert. Jamie will be introduced to the wonders of desert lifestyle to find out how the harsh local terrain has helped to^shape the unique food culture. It will definitely be a crazy ride by spending one day with a caravan of camels and, but all the pay is worth it. Jamie will cook in the VIP desert kitchen and attempt to make the hardest dish to date, for celebrating the unforgettable birthday party.

programme.desc: Down on the sunny coast of Cornwall, world-class, adaptive surfer Peg Leg, wants to do a very unique extension – to his VW campervan home. Despite having no technical training he's hoping to transform his home on wheels by building a new cabin from scratch, for him and his 5 year old daughter, Bluebell.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E4
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchins visit the Chinese province of Yunnan, which contains the largest ethnic diversity in China. 25 minority groups live in the province, and the brothers visit the National Ethnic Minorities Park to learn about and hopefully understand these cultures. To further immerse themselves, they also explore native villages and take part in games, ceremonies and festivals.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E4
programme.desc: Christopher Columbus. Julia Child. Clarence Birdseye. These are some of the revolutionary men and women who have changed what and how we eat, remaking not just food history but human history. Some of these food revolutionaries are well known, others obscure. But one thing they have in common is that they have fundamentally shaped how we live today.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E6
programme.desc: The journey winds through the cradle of Chinese civilization in Shanxi and Shandong. Harry meets a bamboo lantern maker, whose craft is considered one of the intangible cultural heritages of China. He also discovers a kind of ancient housing where people lived in silo caves. As he makes his way to Shandong, Harry helps fishermen to catch and sell shrimp, followed by making giant kites in Weifang.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E9
programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in the Mayan stronghold of the Yucatan Peninsula, major producer of one of the hottest chillies on earth - the Habanero, before heading to the state of Tabasco where chocolate has been consumed for thousands of years.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E9
programme.desc: Sara strolls down memory lane and ranks her top five moments in Australia. From Melbourne, Darwin to Broome and Victoria, she prepares unforgettable delicacies like lamp chop and octopus bashing. Also, she savors unique cuisines like pizza made by alfresco oven. Other than cooking, Sara spends time with a group of kangaroos feeding on grass and also witnesses an alligator hunting for food.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E1
programme.desc: Like the carnival festivals of Rio and Venice, Goa marks the days before Lent with an all-out celebration: three full days of eating, drinking, and partying. David takes part in all of the festivities, including an appearance on a float in Panjim's annual Carnival kick-off parade. He ends up spending time with some Italian expats and celebrating the holiday Venetian-style.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E47
programme.desc: Ben makes a healthy Salmon Poke Bowl and heads down to Huon Aquaculture to see where his salmon has been farmed. Up at The University of Queensland, Joel joins Ben to make a King Fish and Green Olive Dressing, Joel talks to Ben through why fish skin contracts when you place it in a hot pan.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E48
programme.desc: Ben heads to the brand new Clover Hill cellar door in Northern Tasmania and cooks an Asparagus and Roasted Tomato Penne with a paired with glass Clover Hill Vintage Sparkling. Up at the University of Queensland, Ben and Joel prepare a King Fish Sashimi with an easy pickled salad. Back in the studio Ben shows us how to cook one of his favourite cuts of meat, the rump cap paired with some crispy cheesy potatoes.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E5
programme.desc: Turpan, nicknamed the world's sweetest city, is the next leg of Jamie's culinary journey. After lending a hand at a vineyard, and learning what makes these grapes so highly prized, he will risk it all to discover the local secret of what makes this China's largest grape growing region. He also will find the top chefs to teach him three of his favourite Chinese dishes and make a Turpan inspired feast to celebrate the end of harvest.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E6
programme.desc: In this episode, Jamie is at his last stop on the silk road journey, Urumqi, the capital of Xinjiang. He will spend time with the lovely Kazakh friends in the mountains and experience an amazing array of ethnically diverse foods from Kazakh horsemeat to Uyghur baked buns. He will get an exclusive lesson in making everybody's favourite noodle dish and to top it all off, he will cook his own dishes for the most important festival in the Islamic calendar.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E7
programme.desc: Whilst renovating their garage, Steve and wife Marie never dreamt that they would find a World War Two bunker hidden underneath their garden. They decide to revolutionise the damp and dark space into a home office. Steve has devised an ingenious motorised lift that will lift the roof and let in light. Better still when the bunker is not in use the roof goes down and they keep full use of the garden and you'd never know what lies beneath.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E2
programme.desc: Ben is too comfortable behind his desk at Living Color headquarters, so Mat assigns him the job of installing a pair of outsized fish tanks around a fireplace at the Reuss residence in Orlando. What seems like an ordinary job proves to be a challenge for Ben, as he must hone both his client relations and physical skills. Mat leaves for Chicago to work on a terrarium for a rare Panama Golden Frog.

programme.title: Africa's Deadliest: Botswana Compilations E2
programme.desc: Watch out! Roaming the wild battlegrounds of the Kalahari are the Botswana Bullies. These masters of intimidation work alone or in groups. They target other animals, sometimes even their own kind. They dominate, torment and even kill. They are ruthless, bringing conflict and death to this corner of the world.

programme.title: Kingdom Of The White Wolf E1
programme.desc: Ronan Donovan, our expert guide and National Geographic photographer, takes the audience on an intimate exploration of the Arctic during the endless day of the summer months, giving insight to the unexpected abundance of the 'Garden of the Arctic' in Wolf Valley as he attempts to embed with a wolf family pack.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E1
programme.desc: We start on the tiny island of Batan, meeting a unique viper and a ubiquitous but also giant, land crab. Luzon is the main island of the Philippines. We drop in to Mindoro to see the most endangered large mammal in the Philippines, the tamaraw. The bustling capital of Manila dominates the centre of this large island but despite encroachments, huge areas of wilderness still exist. Here we meet blue tarantulas and strange forest birds. In the town of Pulilan we join a celebration that centres on the carabao, water buffalo. In the Verde Passage we join a group of photographers surveying the marine creatures of the area, from frog fish to pygmy seahorses. We also meet the people who have dedicated their lives to saving the most endangered crocodile in the world. On Palawan we find new sea creatures that charm and awe eco-tourists and take a trip along the longest navigable underground river to meet bats and swiftlets. We discover the sad recent history of the Palawan forest turtl.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E2
programme.desc: Ben is too comfortable behind his desk at Living Color headquarters, so Mat assigns him the job of installing a pair of outsized fish tanks around a fireplace at the Reuss residence in Orlando. programme.title: Jungle Heroes E6
programme.desc: Wildlife SOS ended bear dancing in India, rescuing 628 bears from this cruel and illegal trade. Its medical team uses laser massage technology to help a bear that has had a brain haemorrhage, and a rapid response team also rushes to rescue an injured Nilgai - the largest and most dangerous antelope in India. A baby macaque monkey is also found abandoned in a cardboard box next to a highway.

programme.title: Legendary Catch E1
programme.desc: In this chapter of Carter Andrews' life long quest to find and catch the most legendary fish to swim on the planet, he is in hot pursuit of the giant White Sturgeon -- the apex predator in the rivers of the Pacific Northwest. Armed with years of angling knowledge, Carter teams up with different local experts along the way to find the mammoth fish he's after. Will Carter find the legendary fish that history proves have patrolled these rivers for years? Or will he be outwitted by this pre-historic species?

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E1
programme.desc: The Living Color team is challenged to transform a Volkswagen Minibus into a fish tank for car dealer Mike Wetzel. The iconic van is in poor shape, and creating a tank that weighs 1800kg when filled is the most complicated job they've faced. Tempers flare between John and Krusty, leading to his removal from the project. With a tight deadline looming, the team is on the brink of disaster.

programme.title: Wild 24 S2E5
programme.desc: Nearing the end of the wet season, Wild 24 looks at the survival of wildlife in Australia. This episode introduces the Sea Eagle, conqueror of the skies with the ability to pluck fish from the sea and snatch bats whilst in flight. In the billabong lies the largest reptile on Earth, the Salt Water Crocodile, where it is actively pursuing prey or laying quietly for an ambush attack.

programme.title: Kingdom Of The White Wolf E3
programme.desc: Meet the Polygon Pack, a family of arctic wolves surviving and raising young in amidst the polygon ponds of the high arctic.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E2
programme.desc: Moving from turtles of the Palawan coast to the unique National Marine Park at Tubbataha, to meet giants, whale sharks and manta rays. On Bohol we explore the Chocolate hills and met the man who has done more than anyone else to help the Philippine tarsier, a tiny, bug-eyed primate. We also see how people can mediate between people and wildlife as we join a snake hunting team catching and translocating a deadly Samar cobra. On Cebu we join the crowds that come to swim with whale sharks, explore the island home of the sea krait and thrill to see a pelagic thresher shark. On Mindanao we visit a family that have been caring for the endemic Philippine sailfin lizards for many years, so long in fact, that they get 160 or more turning up for breakfast. On Samal island we see the world's greatest concentration of Geoffroys Rousette fruit bats and learn of their value to local farmers. In the South of Mindanao we end with the most iconic Philippine animal of all, the majestic Philipp.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E2
programme.desc: Simon has a close call with a deadly black mamba in the middle of the night and finds his first ever Snouted cobra that's hitchhiked to Durban!

programme.title: Hostile Planet E1
programme.desc: Plenty of water, warmth and light provide perfect conditions for life to thrive and make the jungles the most diverse lands on Earth. But make no mistake, this is no Eden - from Jaguars to Gibbons, Hummingbirds to Orangutans, meet the incredible animals to discover why their struggles for survival in this crowded and competitive world have never been tougher. As jungle seasons become more unpredictable only the toughest animals will triumph.

Tempers flare between John and Krusty, leading to his removal from the project. With a tight deadline looming, the team is on the brink of disaster.

programme.title: Wild 24 S2E5
programme.desc: Nearing the end of the wet season, Wild 24 looks at the survival of wildlife in Australia. This episode introduces the Sea Eagle, conqueror of the skies with the ability to pluck fish from the sea and snatch bats whilst in flight. In the billabong lies the largest reptile on Earth, the Salt Water Crocodile, where it is actively pursuing prey or laying quietly for an ambush attack.

programme.title: Kingdom Of The White Wolf E3
programme.desc: Meet the Polygon Pack, a family of arctic wolves surviving and raising young in amidst the polygon ponds of the high arctic.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E6
programme.desc: Dr. Larry Kawa's office doubles as an orthodontics practice and a multi-aquarium showcase featuring all kinds of rare marine life. Living Color is commissioned to replace the physical tank, and also provide a unique underwater specimen to display. Mat and Francis are stumped and have to dig deep to come up with what is known as a Mermaid's Purse.

programme.title: Africa's Deadliest: Botswana Compilations E3
programme.desc: When you are surrounded by Africa's Deadliest, there can be safety in numbers. Having the protection of fierce group can make the difference between life and death for some animals. But aggression directed outwards can sometimes turn inwards. In this unforgiving land, fierce families fight others, and sometimes amongst themselves, to survive.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S3E5
programme.desc: Snake catchers Simon and Siouxsie discover an 8-foot black mamba after destroying a kitchen for a harmless house snake. Then, they receive a call from a shopping mall that the Africa's largest cobra is loose and causing panic. Finally, a mechanic discovers a deadly snake in his toolbox and it makes his blood cold.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E2
programme.desc: In this dramatic episode of Animal Fight Club, wildlife goes to war, from miniature murderers to the biggest brutes. Using under-the-skin CGI and compelling wildlife footage from some of the world's best documentary makers, we uncover the tactics and strategies behind the brawls. From African plains to the snow-covered wilds of North America, we reveal how nature's deadliest battles are fought over turf, dominance and the right to mate.

programme.desc: Trapped by the rising flood waters, Dikeledi must teach her wayward cubs the lessons of survival. But this brutal Kingdom is no place for a gentle cheetah family. These Wild Dogs have the cunning and experience, but with an ageing leader their strength soon starts to crumble from within and others are waiting to seize their opportunity.

programme.title: Legendary Catch E2
programme.desc: Carter is in the Bolivian jungle in pursuit of a mythical fish that's known for its strength and razor sharp teeth - The Golden Dorado. Pushing himself to the limit, Carter and a local native chief paddle dugout canoes and trek days up a secluded river to an ancient waterfall in the hopes of hooking one of these mystical fish. A formidable foe, Carter sees Dorado and can't hook them. When he can hook a Dorado it's not the legendary size he's after. With supplies running low for his journey, will Carter catch the Dorado he's after?

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E9
programme.desc: Fabio Lisboa, a lifelong fish enthusiast, is looking to make his dreams come true. His vision is a 5000-gallon tank full of sharks. An aquarium that size will not only take up over half of his office, but will be the largest private tank in South Florida. As always, Living Color is up to the challenge.

programme.title: Wild 24 S2E6
programme.desc: Wild 24's journey around the South Seas takes you through the Tropics, South America, and Antarctica. From deadly reefs and a nesting turtle's race to the ocean to a starving baby seal waiting for its mother, this voyage also looks closely at the feeding frenzy whales and penguins which need to put on blubber to survive the harsh winter.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E1
programme.desc: To catch a deadly Black mamba, Simon must face his biggest fear - heights! And to save a spitting cobra, he deals with his OCD and digs in a poo pit!

programme.desc: In this episode of Animal Fight Club, nature gets nasty as the animal kingdom prepares for wild-life warfare. Using remarkable footage, gathered from the world's leading nature documentary makers; combined with stunning, 'under the skin' CGI, we reveal the strategies, techniques and weaponry used when animals fight for their bloodline and survival.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E3
programme.desc: After the murder of one of their own, the Makulu Pack of Wild Dogs looks to a new leader for salvation. The Western Pride is exiled to the fringes the Kingdom as they fight to protect their cubs from enemies on all sides. And as the marauding hyena clan commits the cruelest of acts, their ferocious commander Mmamotse reveals her soft side as she swells her ranks and trains a new army.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E2
programme.desc: Grasslands are some of the most volatile lands on the planet, where animals must endure a seasonal cycle of flood, famine, freeze and fire. We reveal the extraordinary challenges these animals must overcome, and how our changing world is making survival even tougher than before. From epic battles between wolves and bison, to nail biting showdowns between cheetahs and Thompson gazelle fauns, this is an epic tale of life and death in the planet's most dramatic wildernesses.

programme.desc: The birds and the bees have never been so wild. Get ready for alien romance, bizarre reproduction and creative concepts in parenting.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E1
programme.desc: We start on the tiny island of Batan, meeting a unique viper and a ubiquitous but also giant, land crab. Luzon is the main island of the Philippines. We drop in to Mindoro to see the most endangered large mammal in the Philippines, the tamaraw. The bustling capital of Manila dominates the centre of this large island but despite encroachments, huge areas of wilderness still exist. Here we meet blue tarantulas and strange forest birds. In the town of Pulilan we join a celebration that centres on the carabao, water buffalo. In the Verde Passage we join a group of photographers surveying the marine creatures of the area, from frog fish to pygmy seahorses. We also meet the people who have dedicated their lives to saving the most endangered crocodile in the world. On Palawan we find new sea creatures that charm and awe eco-tourists and take a trip along the longest navigable underground river to meet bats and swiftlets. We discover the sad recent history of the Palawan forest turtl.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E10
programme.desc: The Living Color team is in the Bahamas where they've been commissioned to build another ornate, highly specialized aquarium for the Atlantis Casino. They're asking Living Color for an extravagant 4000-pound aquarium for the casinos high-rollers room that will feature one of the ocean's most delicate creatures, the Jelly Fish.

programme.title: Wild 24 S2E2
programme.desc: New Zealand's plants and animals have evolved in ways unlike any other place on Earth with mammals that can fly, birds that refuse to, and creatures with direct linkage to dinosaurs. The strange wildlife through the primeval forests and along the rugged coastline will keep you engaged for the entire 24 hours we spend with them.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E7
programme.desc: While Dr. Oakley awaits a litter of puppies, she hits the road to treat a stubborn bison, and a moose with a respiratory issue. In the clinic, she checks a Great Dane's swollen leg.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E3
programme.desc: In this episode, expect to see how a boy named Jeremy befriends his family cat called Tara, who saved him from a deadly canine attack. Also, a mother dog named Piper formed a maternal bond with her 'goat puppy' called GP, and a man loves to spoil the family's pet deer called Dillie.

programme.title: World's Weirdest S1E1
programme.desc: Take a deep dive into the realm of creepy aquatic creatures to uncover the world's most bizarre water-dwelling tenants. In this episode a fish with a transparent head shows everything it's got. A master-of-disguise octopus camouflages itself to capture prey or elude pursuit. A lizard literally walks on water and a fish walks on dry land... and that's just for starters!

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E2
programme.desc: Moving from turtles of the Palawan coast to the unique National Marine Park at Tubbataha, to meet giants, whale sharks and manta rays. On Bohol we explore the Chocolate hills and met the man who has done more than anyone else to help the Philippine tarsier, a tiny, bug-eyed primate. We also see how people can mediate between people and wildlife as we join a snake hunting team catching and translocating a deadly Samar cobra. On Cebu we join the crowds that come to swim with whale sharks, explore the island home of the sea krait and thrill to see a pelagic thresher shark. On Mindanao we visit a family that have been caring for the endemic Philippine sailfin lizards for many years, so long in fact, that they get 160 or more turning up for breakfast. On Samal island we see the world's greatest concentration of Geoffroys Rousette fruit bats and learn of their value to local farmers. In the South of Mindanao we end with the most iconic Philippine animal of all, the majestic Philipp.
